        "content": "<p>igoriakovlev opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13756\">issue #13756</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h3>Test Case</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/files/29472499/issue.zip\">issue.zip</a></p>\n<h3>Steps to Reproduce</h3>\n<p>Run the following command:<br>\n<code>wasmtime -W gc,exceptions,function-references --dir=/ $PWD/kotlin-wasm-benchmarks-wasmWasiBenchmark.wasm STUB $PWD/config.conf StringBenchmark microBenchmarks.StringBenchmark.stringConcatNullable</code></p>\n<h3>Expected Results</h3>\n<p>Benchmarks are running.</p>\n<h3>Actual Results</h3>\n<p><code>GC heap out of memory: no capacity for allocation of 96 bytes</code> when <code>-C collector=copying</code><br>\n<code>wasm trap: allocation size too large</code> when <code>-C collector=null</code></p>\n<h3>Versions and Environment</h3>\n<p>Wasmtime version or commit: 46.0.1</p>\n<p>Operating system: MacOS 26.5.1</p>\n<p>Architecture: Apple Silicon</p>\n<h3>Extra Info</h3>\n<p>With <code>-C collector=drc</code> benchmarks works good. Seems since 46.0.1 the default GC was changed from drc to copying so tests are now fails.<br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>",
